{
  "texts": [
    "Emerging and endemic pests or pathogens, here collectively referred to as pests* (see Table 1 for definitions of terms marked by an asterisk), are an inseparable component of plant health -in addition to symbioses and abiotic factors, for example.",
    "As such, they are the target of plant health surveillance strategies worldwide.",
    "Rooted in a long history paved with successes and failures, plant health surveillance for emerging or re-emerging pests (simply called \"emerging pests\" hereafter) currently needs both reinforcement and modernization.",
    "This is the central topic of this article.",
    "awareness of the need for more timely and cost-effective response to pest emergence* due to the increasing impact of global change* on pests (Brooks et al. 2022; Carvajal-Yepes et al. 2019; Chaloner et al. 2021; Garrett et al. 2022; Jeger et al. 2021; Morris et al. 2022; Ristaino et al. 2021; Silva et al. 2021; Trivellone et al. 2022)."
  ]
}